Package entities

Class User

java.lang.Object
entities.User
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class User extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a User entity with various attributes such as userId, username, password, email, etc. Implements Serializable interface for object serialization.
Version:
August 2024
Author:
Kfir Amoyal, Israel Ohayon, Yaniv Shatil, Noam Furman, Omri Heit, Eitan Zerbel

    • User

      public User(int userId, String username, String password, String email, String phoneNumber, String permission, String branch, boolean hasDiscountCode, int loggedIn, String accountStatus)
      Parameterized constructor to initialize a User object.
      Parameters:
      userId - the ID of the user
      username - the username of the user
      password - the password of the user
      email - the email of the user
      phoneNumber - the phone number of the user
      permission - the permission level of the user
      branch - the branch associated with the user
      hasDiscountCode - whether the user has a discount code
      loggedIn - the login status of the user (e.g., 1 for logged in, 0 for not)
      accountStatus - the status of the user account (e.g., active, inactive)

    • fromStringArray

      public static ArrayList<User> fromStringArray(String arrayString)
      Creates an ArrayList of User objects from a string representation of an array of Users.

      This method parses a string containing multiple User object representations and converts them into an ArrayList of User objects. Each User object in the string should be in the format produced by the User class's toString() method.

      Parameters:
      arrayString - A string containing one or more User object representations. Each User object should be in the format: "User{userId=X, username='Y', password='Z', ...}"
      Returns:
      An ArrayList of User objects parsed from the input string.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - implicitly if the input string contains User representations that do not match the expected format.
      See Also:
      • fromString(String)
